# Generated Talos machine configs contain PKI material (CA private key,
# bootstrap token, encryption secrets) — never commit them as plaintext.
#
# These are SOPS-encrypted (prod-1 KMS key alias/sops-talos-pki) and the
# encrypted *.sops.yaml versions ARE committed — see terraform/prod-1/sops.tf
# and `task talos:minipc:secrets:{encrypt,decrypt}`. The plaintext below stays
# local-only; regenerate it on a fresh checkout with
# `task talos:minipc:secrets:decrypt`.
#
# controlplane.patch.yaml (the non-secret machine config patch) is committed
# separately. controlplane.patched.yaml is derived (controlplane.yaml + that
# patch) so it's gitignored too — regenerate via the runbook Phase 4 step.
controlplane.yaml
worker.yaml
controlplane.patched.yaml
worker.patched.yaml
talosconfig
secrets.yaml

# Tailscale ExtensionServiceConfig with the real TS_AUTHKEY. Committed only as
# the SOPS-sealed tailscale.patch.sops.yaml; the .example (placeholder key) is
# committed too. Regenerate plaintext via `task talos:minipc:secrets:decrypt`.
tailscale.patch.yaml

# Local backup patterns (zip archives, "copy of" folders, .bak files).
*.zip
*.bak
* copy/
* copy
